20 ACTION, PROCEEDING, PROSECUTION
21
22 SECTION 4. The transfer of duties, functions and powers to the Oregon Department of
23 Emergency Management by section 1 of this 2026 Act does not affect any action, proceeding
24 or prosecution involving or with respect to the duties, functions and powers begun before
25 and pending at the time of the transfer, except that the department is substituted for the
26 Higher Education Coordinating Commission in the action, proceeding or prosecution.
27
28 LIABILITY, DUTY, OBLIGATION
29
30 SECTION 5. (1) Nothing in sections 1 to 4 of this 2026 Act relieves a person of a liability,
31 duty or obligation accruing under or with respect to the duties, functions and powers
32 transferred by section 1 of this 2026 Act. The Oregon Department of Emergency Management
33 may undertake the collection or enforcement of any such liability, duty or obligation.
34 (2) The rights and obligations of the Higher Education Coordinating Commission legally
35 incurred under contracts, leases and business transactions executed, entered into or begun
36 before the operative date of section 1 of this 2026 Act accruing under or with respect to the
37 duties, functions and powers transferred by section 1 of this 2026 Act are transferred to the
38 department. For the purpose of succession to these rights and obligations, the department
39 is a continuation of the commission and not a new authority.
40
41 RULES
42
43 SECTION 6. Notwithstanding the transfer of duties, functions and powers by section 1
44 of this 2026 Act, the rules of the Higher Education Coordinating Commission with respect to
45 such duties, functions or powers that are in effect on the operative date of section 1 of this
