14 OPERATIVE DATE
15
16 SECTION 8. (1) The Director of the Oregon Department of Emergency Management shall
17 notify the standing or interim committees of the Legislative Assembly and the Legislative
18 Counsel when the transfer described in section 1 of this 2026 Act is complete.
19 (2) Sections 1 to 7 of this 2026 Act become operative on the day after the date the no-
20 tifications described in subsection (1) of this section are complete.
21
22 DUTIES OF OREGON DEPARTMENT OF EMERGENCY MANAGEMENT
23
24 SECTION 9. (1) The Oregon Department of Emergency Management shall maintain a
25 statewide registry of persons who are willing and able to volunteer to perform emergency
26 service activities, as defined in ORS 401.358. The registry may include:
27 (a) Qualified emergency service volunteers, as defined in ORS 401.358;
28 (b) Persons registered as volunteers with a local government, as defined in ORS 174.116,
29 or a tribal entity, including members of community emergency response teams and neigh-
30 borhood emergency teams;
31 (c) Persons experienced in construction or other skilled trades;
32 (d) Persons certified by the State Fire Marshal as building evaluators under the Oregon
33 Safety Assessment Program established under ORS 401.256; and
34 (e) Other persons that the department determines are able to assist in emergency re-
35 sponse and recovery.
36 (2) As a condition of inclusion on the registry, the department may require:
37 (a) Evidence of relevant qualifications; and
38 (b) Training related to emergency response and recovery, including incident management
39 or command.
40 (3) The registry must include, for each person:
41 (a) The person’s name and contact information;
42 (b) The physical location where the person is based; and
43 (c) Specialized training or skills related to emergency response and recovery that the
44 person has.
45 (4) The registry must be accessible to emergency management agencies and emergency
[3]

B-Eng. HB 4033
1 program managers described in ORS 401.305. The department may make the registry ac-
2 cessible to any other persons or entities if the department determines that providing such
3 access will enhance public safety.
4 (5) The department is authorized to issue badges to volunteers listed in the registry that
5 describe a volunteer’s skills, training, licenses, certifications or other information relevant
6 to the performance of emergency service activities.
7
8 FISCAL PROVISION
9
10 SECTION 10. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the General Fund appropriation
11 made to the Oregon Department of Emergency Management by section 1 (2), chapter 423,
12 Oregon Laws 2025, for the biennium ending June 30, 2027, for Preparedness and Response, is
13 increased by $32,600, to carry out the provisions of sections 1 and 9 of this 2026 Act.
14
15 CAPTIONS
16
17 SECTION 11. The unit captions used in this 2026 Act are provided only for the conven-
18 ience of the reader and do not become part of the statutory law of this state or express any
19 legislative intent in the enactment of this 2026 Act.
20
21 EFFECTIVE DATE
22
23 SECTION 12. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate preservation of the public
24 peace, health and safety, an emergency is declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect
25 on its passage.
